# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the three keys below.
# Both the CLI (dub.py) and the GUI (python -m gui) load it automatically.
# In Colab you don't edit this file — the notebook writes .env from the
# 🔑 Secrets panel (add the same three names there).
#
# `.env` is gitignored — never commit real keys.

# --- ElevenLabs (Georgian TTS — the only stage that spends real money) ---
# Get it: https://elevenlabs.io -> Profile -> API Keys
# Billed per CHARACTER synthesized; the GUI shows an estimate before spending.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# --- Translation (Dutch -> Georgian, costs pennies per episode) ---
# Set at least ONE of the three below, then pick the provider in the GUI's
# Translate tab (or `translate_provider` in config.yaml). The GUI shows
# which providers are available.

# Anthropic (Claude) — https://console.anthropic.com -> API Keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# OpenAI (GPT) — https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Google (Gemini) — https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# --- HuggingFace (speaker diarization via WhisperX / pyannote) ---
# Get it: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens (a free "read" token is enough)
# You MUST also accept the model licenses ONCE while logged in, or the
# Analyze stage fails with a gated-model error:
#   https://hf.co/pyannote/speaker-diarization-3.1
#   https://hf.co/pyannote/segmentation-3.0
HF_TOKEN=
